DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$n = random(2,7,1);


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \(\displaystyle f(x) = \frac{\ln(x)}{x^{$n}}  \).
For this function there are two important intervals:
 \( (A, B] \) and \( [B,\infty) \) where
 \( A \) and \(B\) are critical numbers or numbers where the function is
undefined.
$BR
Find \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = 0;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
Find \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = exp(1/$n);
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is increasing (type in INC) or decreasing (type in DEC).
$BR
 \( (A, B] \):
 \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "INC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [B,\infty) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
